overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application
  to ensure it met all specified acceptance criteria. The assistant performed a
  detailed analysis, identifying several critical and important missing features
  such as a tiredness severity scale with safety messaging, detection for COMISA
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, weighted EDS scoring, comprehensive CSV
  export, and sections for pain/chronic fatigue and medical/mental health
  history. Following this, the assistant systematically implemented each of
  these identified gaps. This involved modifying data models, validation rules,
  user interface components for input, and the logic for generating both the
  on-screen and PDF reports, ensuring the application now aligns more closely
  with the original requirements and provides more comprehensive patient
  insights.
